In the latest twist in the Gingriches' bitter divorce fight, lawyers for Marianne Gingrich charged in court papers Monday that Gingrich "willfully failed and refused to answer virtually each and every interrogatory concerning his personal and professional relationships as well as the finances of his marriage." This type of question is not uncommon in hard-fought divorce cases, where spouses often hire detectives to sniff out everything from finances to affairs, said Washington divorce lawyer Sanford Ain.
